Consistently ranked among the top ten “Best Firms to Work For” and Engineering News-Record’s top 50 firms worldwide, Langan attracts and retains the best talent in the industry. Employees thrive at Langan, a firm that embraces and promotes diversity, equity and inclusion; prioritizes wellbeing, health and safety; encourages volunteerism and philanthropy; offers workplace flexibility, along with carbon neutral office spaces; and empowers individuals to contribute their skills and knowledge to make impactful contributions.
Job Summary
Langan is seeking a Data Scientist to join its collaborative Information Technology team in Parsippany, NJ. This individual will serve a key function in researching and developing statistical learning models for data analysis using data visualization techniques and tools.
Job Responsibilities
Researches and develops statistical learning models for data analysis and performs manipulations and visualization of business data using visualization tools and techniques;
Collects and interprets data and provides analysis and recommendations;
Performs data analysis to discover trends and patterns;
Works alongside teams within the business or the management team to establish business needs;
Develops custom data models and algorithms to apply to data sets;
Develops processes and tools to monitor and analyze model performance and data accuracy; and
Performs other duties as requested.
Qualifications
Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science, Management Information Systems or a related field;
Experience using statistical computer languages (R, Python, SLQ, etc.) to manipulate data and draw insights from large data sets;
Proficiency in PowerBI\Tableau or other data visualization tools and Microsoft Office (Access, Excel, PowerPoint and Word);
Strong understanding of data mining techniques and an ability to apply these techniques in real-world business issues;
Knowledge of a variety of machine learning techniques and their real-world advantages and drawbacks;
Experience in data models and reporting packages and ability to write comprehensive reports;
Ability to analyze large data sets;
Technical experience with SAP Analytics technologies: S/4HANA Embedded Analytics, BW/4HANA, SAP Fiori is a plus;
Excellent written and verbal communication skills;
Strong attention to detail with excellent, analytical, multitasking, and judgment capabilities; and
Ability to effectively work independently and in a team environment.
